title: PPPP’s Sikander Ali Shoro wins PS-78 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Peoples Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Sikander Ali Shoro has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-78 Jamshoro-II by securing 51,188 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Syed Munir Haider Shah of Grand Democratic Alliance (GDA) who bagged 10,850 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 45.38%.
